Guide to the Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Collection of Communist and Socialist Serials TAM.747

Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Collection of Communist and Socialist Serials

Contents

Series I: American Publications, 1881-2010

Dates:
1881-2010

Extent

68.4 Linear Feet in 89 manuscript boxes, 2 half manuscript boxes, and 102 flat boxes

Scope and Contents

This series collects 1,260 publications -- serials, journals, magazines, newsletters, bulletins, pamphlets, and reports -- issued by a variety of local and national parties, organizations, political organizers, commentators, and affiliated interest groups in the United States. The majority of the series collects regularly published bulletins, newsletters, and newspapers, circulating news and discussion within communities of Communist Party members and activists. One-off reports and occasional papers address a variety of topics in detail, including working regulations, meetings and conventions, and Communist and Socialist movements abroad. Well represented serials in this collection include Burning Spear, Freedom Socialist, The Militant, Socialist Workers Party's Bulletin, and the Central Committee of the Workers League's Bulletin, alongside various titles dedicated to social justice issues intersecting with communist and socialist thought, among them the Gay Socialist Newsletter, Asians in Struggle, and publications dedicated to groups affiliated with the Democratic Socialists of America (including DSA Green News, Socialist Perspectives on Race, and the Democratic Socialists of America Feminist Commission's Not Far Enough).

Arrangement

This series is arranged alphabetically by publishing organization name.

31142063003209box: 248, folder: 5 (Material Type: mixed materials)

Series II: International Publications, 1850-2013

Dates:
1850-2013

Extent

52.6 Linear Feet in 89 manuscript boxes, 1 half manuscript box, and 47 flat boxes

Scope and Contents

This series collects 685 serials and publications issued by Communist and Socialist organizations outside the United States, including in Puerto Rico, Canada, Jamaica, England, Germany, and across the former Soviet Union.

Arrangement

The material in this series is divided into two subseries, organizing material according to its place of publication: Subseries II.A: Soviet Publications; and Subseries II.B: Other International Publications.

Subseries II.A: Soviet Publications, 1920-1999

Dates:
1920-1999

Extent

9.4 Linear Feet in 17 manuscript boxes, 1 half manuscript box, and 6 flat boxes

Scope and Contents

This subseries collects 64 serials and publications originating from the former Soviet Union, predominantly published in Moscow, Russia. The publications encompass news, economic reports, one-off publications memorializing significant leaders and events, and glossy pictorials featuring images of life in the USSR. Titles include Moscow News Weekly, Moscow Daily News, and News and Views, alongside publications issued by organizations including the National Council of American-Soviet Friendship, the USSR Academy of Sciences, Foreign Languages Publishing House, and the Novosti Press Agency.

Arrangement

Material in this subseries is arranged alphabetically by publishing organization name.

Extent

52.6 Linear Feet in 89 manuscript boxes, 1 half manuscript box, and 47 flat boxes

Scope and Contents

This subseries contains 621 serials and publications circulated by communist and socialist groups published outside of the United States or the Soviet Union. Publishing organizations include the Labour Party and Fabian Society of the United Kingdom, the Communist International, China's Foreign Languages Press, and the Communist Parties of Australia, Ireland, Israel, and Italy. This subseries also includes foreign-language titles from Canada, India, Mexico, Nigeria, South Africa, Spain, Sri Lanka, and Switzerland, among other countries.

Arrangement

Materials in this subseries are arranged alphabetically by publishing organization name.
